Working with Tabs

Create New tab

  •  When object is in edit mode next to the title of the existing tab there is + sign that allows the user to create new tab.
  •  When Create new tab (the + sign) is selected then automatically Tab Configuration screen is opened.
  •  In the Configuration screen there is Tab title field, where you can change the title of the tab.
  •  When the Configuration screen is closed (select Save button)  a new tab is created and the user is automatically positioned in the new tab.

Configure visible sections in tab

  • Configurations can be set during the tab creation or after that.
  • When object is in edit mode, next to the tab title you can click and open the actions available on the tab.
  • When I select Configure option a popup screen opens with the tab configuration.
  • In the Configuration screen there is Visible Tab Sections, where you can check/ uncheck the sections you want to see. By default Navigation and Comments are checked to be visible. The Content section could not be hidden.
  • If you uncheck Comments section then on the tab are visible only the Navigation and the Content sections.
  • If I uncheck Navigation section then on the tab are visible only the Content and Comments sections.
  • If both Navigation and Comments sections are unchecked, then on the tab is visible only the Content section, expanded on entire screen.
  • There are Save and Cancel buttons at the bottom of the Configuration screen.
  • When Save is selected then the changes in the configuration are applied in the tab.
  • When Cancel is selected then the changes in the configuration are not saved and not applied in the tab.

    Lock tab for edit

    • You are able to lock some of the tabs in the object if you do not want to be edited from other users who have edit permissions on the object.
    • This functionality is especially for the templates that are created for objects, because templates include tabs with system information taht is better to be not edited/deleted from the normal users.
    • For example you want for every cultural object to have tabs with special information like the Dashboards, Properties tab and Relationships, which you do not want to be easily deleted/ edited.
      • In the Configuration screen for each tab there is option: Lock tab.
      • When a tab is locked then the text editor is hidden in the tab and users could not inserts new widgets, edit/ insert text.
      • When a tab is locked the users could not delete and configure widgets (only collapse/ expand widget option is available).
      • When a tab is locked the users still could enter/edit data in the widgets content.
      • When a tab is locked the Delete tab action is hidden.
      • When a tab is locked its Title could not be edited.
      • When a new tab is created, it is created as unlocked by default.
      • When a tab is locked and a template is created, then the instances are created with locked tabs also.

    Reorder tabs

    • Tabs are reordered when the user drags and drops them
    • Tabs could be reordered only when an object is in edit mode.
    • Both locked for edit and unlocked tabs could be reordered
    • The new order of the tabs is saved when the object is saved. If the edit is canceled the previous order of the tabs is displayed.

    Delete tab

    • There is Delete action in the actions list of a tab.
    • The action is active only for objects in edit mode and the tab is unlocked.
    • When a tab is deleted it is deleted with all its content.
    • The actual delete happens only when the object is saved. If the edit is canceled, then the tab will remain.
    • When the action Delete is selected, then a confirmation message is displayed.
    • If there is only one tab it could not be deleted.

    Configure revision visibility of the tab

    • When publish an object, the revision includes tabs, that are previously configured.
    • All tabs in the original object, for which is configured Export tab in the revision, are exported in single PDF based on the order of the tabs in the original object and are uploaded in the revision.
    • All tabs in the original object for which is configured Clone tab in the revision are cloned in the revision (the tab is cloned with its content and widgets, and the widgets are updated data related with the revision). The cloned tabs are displayed after the Revision content tab in the order, they exist in original object.
